# Vercel Environment Variables Example
# Add these to your Vercel project via CLI or Dashboard

# ============================================
# FIREBASE SERVICE ACCOUNT CREDENTIALS
# ============================================
# Get these from Firebase Console:
# Project Settings → Service Accounts → Generate New Private Key

FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=firebase-adminsdk-xxxxx@your-project.iam.gserviceaccount.com
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYOUR_PRIVATE_KEY_HERE\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"

# ============================================
# CLICKPAY CREDENTIALS
# ============================================
# Get these from ClickPay Dashboard:
# Developers → API Keys

CLICKPAY_SERVER_KEY=your_clickpay_server_key_here
CLICKPAY_PROFILE_ID=your_profile_id_here
CLICKPAY_API_URL=https://secure.clickpay.com.sa

# ============================================
# HOW TO ADD TO VERCEL
# ============================================

# Method 1: Via CLI
# ------------------
# vercel env add FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID
# vercel env add FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL  
# vercel env add FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY
# vercel env add CLICKPAY_SERVER_KEY
# vercel env add CLICKPAY_PROFILE_ID
# vercel env add CLICKPAY_API_URL

# Method 2: Via Dashboard
# -----------------------
# 1. Go to https://vercel.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Settings → Environment Variables
# 4. Add each variable above
# 5. Select "Production", "Preview", and "Development"
# 6. Save

# ============================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES
# ============================================
# 
# 1. FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY must include the quotes and \n newlines
#    Example: "-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nMIIEvQ...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"
#
# 2. Do NOT commit .env or .env.local files to Git
#
# 3. Client-side Firebase config goes in collect/firebase-config.js
#    (Those are safe to expose in client-side code)
#
# 4. After adding env vars, redeploy:
#    vercel --prod



